## Pattern Examples: Structured Logging in `api/platform` and `apps/platform`

---

### 1. Import — always the same single line

**Found in every file that logs**, e.g.:
- `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/api/platform/src/inngest/functions/health-check.ts:18`
- `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/api/platform/src/lib/oauth/authorize.ts:10`
- `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/api/platform/src/lib/oauth/callback.ts:13`
- `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/api/platform/src/lib/jobs.ts:20`
- `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/apps/platform/src/app/api/connect/[provider]/callback/route.ts:15`

```ts
import { log } from "@vendor/observability/log/next";
```

There is no `createLogger()` call and no instantiation step. `log` is a module-level singleton exported from `@vendor/observability/log/next`.

---

### 2. What the singleton actually is

**Found in**: `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/vendor/observability/src/log/next.ts`

```ts
import "server-only";

import { log as logtail } from "@logtail/next";
import { betterstackEnv } from "../env/betterstack";

const shouldUseBetterStack = betterstackEnv.VERCEL_ENV === "production";

export const log = shouldUseBetterStack ? logtail : console;

export type Logger = typeof log;
```

The `Logger` interface is defined in `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/vendor/observability/src/log/types.ts`:

```ts
export interface Logger {
  debug: (message: string, metadata?: Record<string, unknown>) => void;
  error: (message: string, metadata?: Record<string, unknown>) => void;
  info: (message: string, metadata?: Record<string, unknown>) => void;
  warn: (message: string, metadata?: Record<string, unknown>) => void;
}
```

---

### 3. Call signature — all methods

Every call follows the same shape: `log.level("[module/context] description", { ...fields })`.

The first argument is always a string prefixed with a `[bracket-namespaced-tag]`. The second argument is always an inline object literal with named context fields — never positional arguments or template literals.

---

### Concrete Example 1: `health-check.ts` — `.info()` and `.warn()` in an Inngest function

**Found in**: `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/api/platform/src/inngest/functions/health-check.ts`

```ts
// line 57 — top-level count log before a loop
log.info("[health-check] probing installations", {
  count: installations.length,
});

// line 75 — skip with context inside a step
log.warn("[health-check] provider not configured — skipping", {
  provider: providerName,
  installationId: installation.id,
});

// line 123 — success result with ID and provider
log.info("[health-check] healthy", {
  installationId: installation.id,
  provider: providerName,
});

// line 131 — auth failure with enum value for status
log.warn("[health-check] auth failure — firing lifecycle", {
  installationId: installation.id,
  provider: providerName,
  status,
});

// line 187 — in a private helper, includes computed derived fields
log.warn("[health-check] transient failure recorded", {
  installationId: installation.id,
  provider: installation.provider,
  newFailureCount,
  healthStatus,
});
```

---

### Concrete Example 2: `authorize.ts` — `.warn()` only (lib function with no happy-path log)

**Found in**: `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/api/platform/src/lib/oauth/authorize.ts`

```ts
// line 67 — unknown provider
log.warn("[oauth/authorize] provider not configured", { provider });

// line 76 — redirect_to validation failure, URL not on allowlist
log.warn("[oauth/authorize] invalid redirect_to (not on allowlist)", {
  provider,
  redirectTo,
});

// line 83 — redirect_to malformed
log.warn("[oauth/authorize] invalid redirect_to (malformed URL)", {
  provider,
  redirectTo,
});

// line 114 — wrong auth kind
log.warn("[oauth/authorize] provider does not support OAuth", { provider });
```

Note: the happy path (successful URL build) has no `log.info` in the lib layer — that log lives in the route handler layer at `apps/platform/src/app/api/connect/[provider]/authorize/route.ts:52`.

---

### Concrete Example 3: `callback.ts` — `.warn()`, `.info()`, and `.error()` together

**Found in**: `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/api/platform/src/lib/oauth/callback.ts`

```ts
// line 166 — guard at the top
log.warn("[oauth/callback] provider not configured", {
  provider: providerName,
});

// line 210 — state token sanitized before logging (first 8 chars only)
log.warn("[oauth/callback] invalid or expired state", {
  provider: providerName,
  state: state ? `${state.slice(0, 8)}...` : "empty",
});

// line 222 — mismatch between URL and state
log.warn("[oauth/callback] state provider mismatch", {
  provider: providerName,
  stateProvider: stateData.provider,
});

// line 266 — info on a non-error branch
log.info("[oauth/callback] pending setup, redirecting", {
  provider: providerName,
  setupAction: result.setupAction,
});

// line 345 — success
log.info("[oauth/callback] connected", {
  provider: providerName,
  reactivated,
});

// line 354 — catch block, error extracted to string before logging
log.error("[oauth/callback] oauth callback failed", {
  provider: providerName,
  error: message,   // message = err instanceof Error ? err.message : "unknown"
});
```

---

### Concrete Example 4: `jobs.ts` — error in catch blocks and info on success

**Found in**: `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/api/platform/src/lib/jobs.ts`

```ts
// line 47 — validation failure with structured zod error
log.error("[jobs] invalid workflow input", {
  error: validated.error.format(),
  input: params.input,
});

// line 61 — idempotency check hit, returns early
log.info("[jobs] job already exists", {
  jobId: existing.id,
  inngestRunId: params.inngestRunId,
});

// line 88 — successful creation
log.info("[jobs] job created", {
  jobId: job.id,
  inngestRunId: params.inngestRunId,
  name: params.name,
});

// line 96 — catch block, raw error object passed directly
log.error("[jobs] failed to create job record", {
  error,
  inngestRunId: params.inngestRunId,
  name: params.name,
});

// line 130 — status transition
log.info("[jobs] job status updated", { jobId, status });

// line 132 — catch for the same operation
log.error("[jobs] failed to update job status", { error, jobId, status });

// line 206 — completion with derived duration field
log.info("[jobs] job completed", {
  jobId: params.jobId,
  status: params.status,
  durationMs,
});
```

---

### Summary of conventions

| Aspect | Pattern |
|---|---|
| Import path | `@vendor/observability/log/next` |
| Import name | `log` (always destructured, never aliased) |
| Instantiation | None — `log` is a module singleton |
| Message format | `"[module/submodule] human description"` — bracket-prefixed tag |
| Context argument | Inline object literal `{ key, key2, ... }` — second positional arg |
| `.error()` in catch | Raw `error` object passed as `{ error }`, or `err.message` extracted to a string first |
| Sensitive values | Truncated before logging — e.g., `state.slice(0, 8) + "..."` (callback.ts:210) |
| Happy path in lib vs route | Lib logs `.warn`/`.error` for failures; some `.info` success logs live in the route handler layer instead |

